		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Gaze of the Third Eye",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>The Morvudd targets a creature within 60 feet of him, focusing its gaze upon them. Target creature must attempt at a @Check[will|dc:31|traits:incapacitation,mental,occult,visual] save. If the creature fails, they're subjected randomly to one of the following effects, chosen before the target attempts at the saving throw.</p><hr /><p> 1. <em>Asleep</em>, the target fall @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fBnFDH2MTzgFijKf]{Unconscious} until the end of their next turn, dropping everything it holds and falling @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone}. They wakes up if they takes any damage or if another creature use a manipulate action to wake them up. 2. <em>Madness</em> the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.yblD8fOR1J8rDwEQ]{Confused} until the end of its next turn (or for 1 minute if they critically fails). 3. <em>Dazed</em> The target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.6uEgoh53GbXuHpTF]{Paralyzed} until the end of their next turn. (They're paralyzed for 1 minute with a critical failure, and can attempt a new saving throw at the end of each turn to free themselves). 4. <em>Weakened</em> The target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 1} until the end of their next turn (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 2} with a critical failure).</p><p></p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
